  "steps": [
    {
      "id": "l5-food-theory",
      "type": "theory",
      "title": "Food and drink",
      "body": "# Essen und Trinken — food and drink\n\n| German | English |\n|---|---|\n| **das Brot** | the bread |\n| **das Wasser** | the water |\n| **der Kaffee** | the coffee |\n| **der Apfel** | the apple |\n| **die Milch** | the milk |\n| **der Käse** | the cheese |\n\nWatch the spelling of **Käse** (with **ä**). As always, learn each noun with its article (**der / die / das**)."
    },
    {
      "id": "l5-phrases-theory",
      "type": "theory",
      "title": "Useful everyday phrases",
      "body": "# Everyday phrases\n\nThese phrases will get you through a café, a shop, or a tricky conversation:\n\n- **Ich möchte …** — *I would like …* (polite ordering)\n- **Die Rechnung, bitte.** — *The bill, please.*\n- **Entschuldigung.** — *Excuse me / Sorry.*\n- **Wie viel kostet das?** — *How much does it cost?*\n- **Ich verstehe nicht.** — *I don't understand.*\n- **Sprechen Sie Englisch?** — *Do you speak English?*\n\nNotice the **ö** in *möchte* and the capitalised **Sie** (the formal \"you\")."
    },
    {
